places.name: Owen Roberts International Airport
places.perex: Owen Roberts International Airport is an airport located in Grand Cayman, Cayman Islands.

places.name: Seven Mile Beach
places.perex: Seven Mile Beach is a long crescent of coral-sand beach on the western end of Grand Cayman island.

places.name: East End Lighthouse Park
places.perex: The East End Light is a lighthouse located at the east end of Grand Cayman island in the Cayman Islands.

places.name: Cayman Turtle Farm
places.perex: A great amusement park that is mainly focused on turtles, you will see all kinds, sizes and shapes of them here.

places.name: Queen Elizabeth II Botanic Park
places.perex: Queen Elizabeth II Botanic Park is a non-profit outdoor garden and wildlife facility located in the North Side District of Grand Cayman…

places.name: Fort George
places.perex: Fort George is a colonial era fortification located on Grand Cayman, Cayman Islands.

places.name: Stingray City
places.perex: Stingray City est un banc de sable submergé au large de Grand Cayman, aux îles Caïmans, connu pour son importante population de raies.

places.name: Mission House Historic Site
places.perex: The Mission House is a historic house located in Bodden Town, Grand Cayman.

places.name: Seven Fathoms Rum
places.perex: If you want to see the distillery where Caribbean rum is made, this is the right place. You can book a tour or take a self-guided one.

places.name: Kittiwake Shipwreck & Artificial Reef
places.perex: An US navy ship that was sunk to create an artificial reef for scuba divers and snorkelers. It is great adventure to dive inside.

places.name: East End Light
places.perex: The East End Light is a lighthouse located at the east end of Grand Cayman island in the Cayman Islands.

places.name: Peace Memorial
places.perex: A peace memorial built in 1919 to commemorate the end of 1st World War. In front of it is a small Clock Tower.

places.name: Star Fish Beach
places.perex: This beach is famous because you can find starfish everywhere, when you visit it. Recommended!

places.name: Dolphin Cove
places.perex: Lots of people dream of swimming with dolphins, here you can fulfill the dream and enjoy it. You will never forget this experience.

places.name: Doc Polson Wreck
places.perex: Another of many wrecks used for diving close to Grand Cayman shore. This is a great place for taking photos, you can dive inside the wreck.

places.name: Royal Palms Beach Bar & Reef Grill
Clifton Hunter High School
places.perex: Clifton Hunter High School is a senior high school in Frank Sound, North Side, Grand Cayman, Cayman Islands.

places.name: Malportas Pond
places.perex: Malportas Pond is a salt-water pond on the north coast of Grand Cayman, Cayman Islands, near North Side village.

places.name: Haig Bodden Stadium
places.perex: Haig Bodden Stadium is a football facility located in Bodden Town, Cayman Islands.

places.name: Rum Point Beach
places.perex: A peninsula full of beaches suitable for kids. It is a great place with restaurants, so you can get some food after your day on the beach.

places.name: Blow Holes Diving Site
places.perex: Underground caverns filled with hot water are creating impressive geysers here. You should not miss it.

places.name: Cayman Islands National Museum
places.perex: A museum that is dedicated to the history and heritage of Cayman Islands. Its exhibitions include both human and nature history.

places.name: Pedro St. James National Historic Site
places.name_suffix: Saint James Pedro Castle, Îles Caïmans
places.perex: The oldest building on the Cayman Islands, former English colonist seat, that is preserving their cultural and historical heritage.

places.name: The Cayman Islands Brewery
places.perex: You would be surprised that even here you can find a brewery. If you want to find out their way of brewing beer, take their tour.

places.name: Watler's Cemetery
places.perex: In the past inhabitants of Cayman Islands made their cemeteries on the beaches. This is the most important one.

places.name: Cemetery Beach and Reef
places.perex: Another place that offers a perfect place for snorkeling, swimming and sunbathing. The underwater life here is gorgeous.

places.name: Dolphin Discovery
places.perex: Dolphins are beautiful and cute animals, and here you have the opportunity to enjoy dolphin shows as well as swimming with them.

places.perex: The Old Savannah School House is a historic one-room schoolhouse in Grand Cayman, Cayman Islands.

places.name: Mastic Reserve & Trail
places.perex: This reserve contains dry forests and a trail through it. If you want to explore the nature of Grand Cayman, this is a perfect place.

places.name: Spirit of the West, West Bay Horseriding
places.perex: Here you can book horse rides on the beach or even swimming along the beach on them.

places.name: Cayman Motor Museum
places.perex: A museum, that is showing very rare and unique vehicles such as the original Batmobile from the movie, Rolls-Royces, Bentleys and many…

places.name: Tips N Toes Spa
places.perex: Professional and nice staff will make you relax during one of their massages or during beauty procedures in this spa.

places.name: National Gallery of the Cayman Islands
places.perex: Although most of the pieces of art are imported, some of them are also from Cayman Islands. This gallery is definitely worth visiting.

places.name: Governor Michael Gore Bird Sanctuary
places.perex: Great place for nature lovers. This reserve is famous for various species of birds that have their nesting places here.

places.name: Eden Rock Diving Site
places.perex: This diving site is very popular thanks to small caverns that are perfect for scuba diving. The feeling of diving here is indescribable.

places.name: Bloody Bay Wall Diving Site
places.perex: One of the top diving locations in the Cayman islands. If you want to see the underwater world, this is one of the best choices you can make.

places.name: White Sand Water Sports
places.perex: If you want to enjoy some fun or adrenaline, here you can try great attractions such as wowballs of seabobs.

places.name: Tarpon Lake
places.perex: This lake is a perfect place for a fishing trip, tarpon fish lives here and you will be proud of yourself if you catch it.

places.name: Blossom Village
places.perex: A small village on the Little Cayman with traditional cottages. It has small but cozy beaches suitable for swimming.

places.name: Rebecca's Cave
places.perex: A small cave with a tombstone inside. The sad history of the place says that a young girl died here during the hurricane in 1932.

places.name: Lea's Lookout Diving Site
places.perex: Another great diving place, where you can explore the beauties of underwater life. Turtles and fish will be yor company during your dive.

places.name: Little Cayman Baptist Church
places.perex: The only church on Little Cayman, it is nothing special, but if you want, you can go to visit it. It is oldest standing building on island.

places.name: Oro Verde Wreck
places.perex: A ship that was intentionally sunk in order to create an interesting diving place.

places.name: Sandy Point Beach
places.perex: A beautiful beach that is usually not so busy as other beaches here. It is a great place to spend a day swimming and sunbathing.

places.name: Nancy's Cup of Tea Diving Site
places.perex: A dive site accessible only by boat that looks really amazing with all the marine life. Lots of fish and beautiful cliffs.

places.name: Randy's Gazebo Diving Site
places.perex: A popular diving place where you can see a seahorse residence. It is fascinating to see these beautiful animals in their natural habitat.

places.name: Booby Pond Nature Reserve
places.perex: A nature reserve, which is the largest nesting place of endangered Red-footed Boobies in whole Caribbean. Great for bird-watchers.

places.name: MV Captain Keith Tibbetts Wreck
places.perex: This huge Russian frigate is another of many wrecks that are popular destinations for divers from all over the world.

places.name: Mixing Bowl Diving Site
places.perex: A place where reefs meet corals and cliffs. The marine life here is simply spectacular so it is perfect place for diving.

places.name: Lighthouse Footpath
places.perex: A beautiful hiking trail, where you can enjoy amazing scenery while climbing the cliff as well as see birds nesting.

places.name: Cayman Brac Parrot & Reserve
places.perex: Here you can see the protected parrots in their natural habitat. It is fascinating to see this beautiful animals.

places.name: Cayman Brac Museum
places.perex: This museum is focused on history, you can see various artifacts as well as some documents and special exposition on 1932 hurricane.

places.name: The Bluff Diving Site
places.perex: Beautiful cliffs that are the main dominant of Cayman Brac. If you climb them, you will be rewarded with amazing scenery.

places.name: Cayman Maritime Treasure Museum
places.perex: A history museum that deals mainly with boat building, turtling and also pirates. Its collection includes interesting maps.
